  </section>

  <section class="left">
    <h2 class="slide-in-from-left animate">High-Strength Carbon Nanotube Threads</h2>
  </section>

  <section class="right">
    <p class="slide-in-from-right animate"><strong>At 100 gigapascals and greater,</strong> we are making continuous carbon nanotube threads that are safe, strong, light, flexible, and have many applications across products and industries.</p>
    <img class="slide-in-from-right animate" src={CntThread2} alt="">
    <a class="button button-light slide-in-from-right animate" href="#high-strength-carbon-nanotube-threads">Coming Soon</a>
  </section>

  <section class="left">
    <h2 class="slide-in-from-left animate">The Material Of The Future</h2>
  </section>

  <section class="right">
    <p class="slide-in-from-right animate"><strong>Carbon nanotubes</strong> are one of the most innovative materials ever invented and stand ready to disrupt everything from tennis racquets to spacecraft, sailboat racing, aerospace, automotive, and far beyond.</p>
    <ul class="slide-in-from-right animate">
      <li class="slide-in-from-right animate">30x stronger than kevlar, 20x&nbsp;stronger than carbon fiber</li>
      <li class="slide-in-from-right animate">High chemical resistance</li>
      <li class="slide-in-from-right animate">Light-weight</li>
      <li class="slide-in-from-right animate">Readily workable</li>
      <li class="slide-in-from-right animate">Incredibly flexible</li>
      <li class="slide-in-from-right animate">Conductive or EM shielding</li>
      <li class="slide-in-from-right animate">From 1 mm up to 2 cm long</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="slide-in-from-right animate">Imagine a plane twice the size and half the weight of a 747, an untwistable golf club, an unbendable tennis racket, an inflatable space habitat system. Carbon nanotubes can enable each of these and more.</p>
